aaload.description: load onto the stack a reference from an array

aastore.description: store a reference in an array

aconst_null.description: push a null reference onto the stack

aload.description: load a reference onto the stack from a local variable #index

aload_0.description: load a reference onto the stack from local variable 0

aload_1.description: load a reference onto the stack from local variable 1

aload_2.description: load a reference onto the stack from local variable 2

aload_3.description: load a reference onto the stack from local variable 3

anewarray.description: create a new array of references of length count and component type identified by the class reference index (.mw-parser-output .monospaced{font-family:monospace,monospace}indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2) in the constant pool

areturn.description: return a reference from a method

arraylength.description: get the length of an array

astore.description: store a reference into a local variable #index

astore_0.description: store a reference into local variable 0

astore_1.description: store a reference into local variable 1

astore_2.description: store a reference into local variable 2

astore_3.description: store a reference into local variable 3

athrow.description: throws an error or exception (notice that the rest of the stack is cleared, leaving only a reference to the Throwable)

baload.description: load a byte or Boolean value from an array

bastore.description: store a byte or Boolean value into an array

bipush.description: push a byte onto the stack as an integer value

breakpoint.description: reserved for breakpoints in Java debuggers; should not appear in any class file

caload.description: load a char from an array

castore.description: store a char into an array

checkcast.description: checks whether an objectref is of a certain type, the class reference of which is in the constant pool at index (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

d2f.description: convert a double to a float

d2i.description: convert a double to an int

d2l.description: convert a double to a long

daload.description: load a double from an array

dastore.description: store a double into an array

dconst_0.description: push the constant 0.0 (a double) onto the stack

dconst_1.description: push the constant 1.0 (a double) onto the stack

dload.description: load a double value from a local variable #index

dload_0.description: load a double from local variable 0

dload_1.description: load a double from local variable 1

dload_2.description: load a double from local variable 2

dload_3.description: load a double from local variable 3

drem.description: get the remainder from a division between two doubles

dreturn.description: return a double from a method

dstore.description: store a double value into a local variable #index

dstore_0.description: store a double into local variable 0

dstore_1.description: store a double into local variable 1

dstore_2.description: store a double into local variable 2

dstore_3.description: store a double into local variable 3

dup.description: duplicate the value on top of the stack

dup_x1.description: insert a copy of the top value into the stack two values from the top. value1 and value2 must not be of the type double or long.

dup_x2.description: insert a copy of the top value into the stack two (if value2 is double or long it takes up the entry of value3, too) or three values (if value2 is neither double nor long) from the top

dup2.description: duplicate top two stack words (two values, if value1 is not double nor long; a single value, if value1 is double or long)

dup2_x1.description: duplicate two words and insert beneath third word (see explanation above)

dup2_x2.description: duplicate two words and insert beneath fourth word

f2d.description: convert a float to a double

f2i.description: convert a float to an int

f2l.description: convert a float to a long

faload.description: load a float from an array

fastore.description: store a float in an array

fload.description: load a float value from a local variable #index

fload_0.description: load a float value from local variable 0

fload_1.description: load a float value from local variable 1

fload_2.description: load a float value from local variable 2

fload_3.description: load a float value from local variable 3

frem.description: get the remainder from a division between two floats

fstore.description: store a float value into a local variable #index

fstore_0.description: store a float value into local variable 0

fstore_1.description: store a float value into local variable 1

fstore_2.description: store a float value into local variable 2

fstore_3.description: store a float value into local variable 3

getfield.description: get a field value of an object objectref, where the field is identified by field reference in the constant pool index (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

getstatic.description: get a static field value of a class, where the field is identified by field reference in the constant pool index (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

goto.description: goes to another instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

goto_w.description: goes to another instruction at branchoffset (signed int constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 24 | branchbyte2 << 16 | branchbyte3 << 8 | branchbyte4)

i2b.description: convert an int into a byte

i2c.description: convert an int into a character

i2d.description: convert an int into a double

i2f.description: convert an int into a float

i2l.description: convert an int into a long

i2s.description: convert an int into a short

iaload.description: load an int from an array

iand.description: perform a bitwise AND on two integers

iastore.description: store an int into an array

iconst_m1.description: load the int value −1 onto the stack

iconst_0.description: load the int value 0 onto the stack

iconst_1.description: load the int value 1 onto the stack

iconst_2.description: load the int value 2 onto the stack

iconst_3.description: load the int value 3 onto the stack

iconst_4.description: load the int value 4 onto the stack

iconst_5.description: load the int value 5 onto the stack

if_acmpeq.description: if references are equal, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

if_acmpne.description: if references are not equal, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

if_icmpeq.description: if ints are equal, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

if_icmpge.description: if value1 is greater than or equal to value2, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

if_icmpgt.description: if value1 is greater than value2, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

if_icmple.description: if value1 is less than or equal to value2, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

if_icmplt.description: if value1 is less than value2, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

if_icmpne.description: if ints are not equal, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

ifeq.description: if value is 0, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

ifge.description: if value is greater than or equal to 0, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

ifgt.description: if value is greater than 0, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

ifle.description: if value is less than or equal to 0, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

iflt.description: if value is less than 0, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

ifne.description: if value is not 0, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

ifnonnull.description: if value is not null, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

ifnull.description: if value is null, branch to instruction at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2)

iinc.description: increment local variable #index by signed byte const

iload.description: load an int value from a local variable #index

iload_0.description: load an int value from local variable 0

iload_1.description: load an int value from local variable 1

iload_2.description: load an int value from local variable 2

iload_3.description: load an int value from local variable 3

impdep1.description: reserved for implementation-dependent operations within debuggers; should not appear in any class file

impdep2.description: reserved for implementation-dependent operations within debuggers; should not appear in any class file

instanceof.description: determines if an object objectref is of a given type, identified by class reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

invokedynamic.description: invokes a dynamic method and puts the result on the stack (might be void); the method is identified by method reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

invokeinterface.description: invokes an interface method on object objectref and puts the result on the stack (might be void); the interface method is identified by method reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

invokespecial.description: invoke instance method on object objectref and puts the result on the stack (might be void); the method is identified by method reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

invokestatic.description: invoke a static method and puts the result on the stack (might be void); the method is identified by method reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

invokevirtual.description: invoke virtual method on object objectref and puts the result on the stack (might be void); the method is identified by method reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

ireturn.description: return an integer from a method

jsr†.description: jump to subroutine at branchoffset (signed short constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 8 | branchbyte2) and place the return address on the stack

jsr_w†.description: jump to subroutine at branchoffset (signed int constructed from unsigned bytes branchbyte1 << 24 | branchbyte2 << 16 | branchbyte3 << 8 | branchbyte4) and place the return address on the stack

l2d.description: convert a long to a double

l2f.description: convert a long to a float

l2i.description: convert a long to a int

laload.description: load a long from an array

lastore.description: store a long to an array

lcmp.description: push 0 if the two longs are the same, 1 if value1 is greater than value2, -1 otherwise

lconst_0.description: push 0L (the number zero with type long) onto the stack

lconst_1.description: push 1L (the number one with type long) onto the stack

ldc.description: push a constant #index from a constant pool (String, int, float, Class, java.lang.invoke.MethodType, java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle, or a dynamically-computed constant) onto the stack

ldc_w.description: push a constant #index from a constant pool (String, int, float, Class, java.lang.invoke.MethodType, java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle, or a dynamically-computed constant) onto the stack (wide index is constructed as indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

ldc2_w.description: push a constant #index from a constant pool (double, long, or a dynamically-computed constant) onto the stack (wide index is constructed as indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

lload.description: load a long value from a local variable #index

lload_0.description: load a long value from a local variable 0

lload_1.description: load a long value from a local variable 1

lload_2.description: load a long value from a local variable 2

lload_3.description: load a long value from a local variable 3

lookupswitch.description: a target address is looked up from a table using a key and execution continues from the instruction at that address

lrem.description: remainder of division of two longs

lshl.description: bitwise shift left of a long value1 by int value2 positions

lshr.description: bitwise shift right of a long value1 by int value2 positions

lstore.description: store a long value in a local variable #index

lstore_0.description: store a long value in a local variable 0

lstore_1.description: store a long value in a local variable 1

lstore_2.description: store a long value in a local variable 2

lstore_3.description: store a long value in a local variable 3

lushr.description: bitwise shift right of a long value1 by int value2 positions, unsigned

monitorenter.description: enter monitor for object ("grab the lock" – start of synchronized() section)

monitorexit.description: exit monitor for object ("release the lock" – end of synchronized() section)

multianewarray.description: create a new array of dimensions dimensions of type identified by class reference in constant pool index (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2); the sizes of each dimension is identified by count1, [count2, etc.]

new.description: create new object of type identified by class reference in constant pool index (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

newarray.description: create new array with count elements of primitive type identified by atype

pop.description: discard the top value on the stack

pop2.description: discard the top two values on the stack (or one value, if it is a double or long)

putfield.description: set field to value in an object objectref, where the field is identified by a field reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

putstatic.description: set static field to value in a class, where the field is identified by a field reference index in constant pool (indexbyte1 << 8 | indexbyte2)

ret†.description: continue execution from address taken from a local variable #index (the asymmetry with jsr is intentional)

sipush.description: push a short onto the stack as an integer value

swap.description: swaps two top words on the stack (note that value1 and value2 must not be double or long)

tableswitch.description: continue execution from an address in the table at offset index

wide.description: execute opcode, where opcode is either iload, fload, aload, lload, dload, istore, fstore, astore, lstore, dstore, or ret, but assume the index is 16 bit; or execute iinc, where the index is 16 bits and the constant to increment by is a signed 16 bit short

(no name).description: these values are currently unassigned for opcodes and are reserved for future use
